column5: The past few days off Port Maitland has been good for Walleye ...but dam are the Fleas a pain in the butt this summer ...68 to 85 fow water has been very good for Big Walleye ...best rigs have been 10 Color Core with a Worm Harness and Small Dipsys on a 3 setting back 130 to 150 ...get out and enjoy what Lake Erie has to offer off Port Maitland ...
